From b1553dcae1ef8d25801aa965ae8af1b09f54420e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sebastian Patino-Lang <sebastian.patino-lang@posteo.net>
Date: Thu, 26 Feb 2026 11:16:07 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add early file validation with provider-specific
 constraints

Each LLM provider now declares a FileConstraints struct (supported image
types, max sizes accounting for base64 inflation). PostToAIPost validates
every attached file against these constraints before fetching content.
Unsupported or oversized files produce a structured note in the message
so the bot can inform the user, instead of being silently dropped or
causing API errors.

- Add FileConstraints struct and interface method to LanguageModel
- Implement FileConstraints on Anthropic, OpenAI, Bedrock, ASage
- Add FileConstraints delegation to all LanguageModel wrappers
- Rewrite file loop in PostToAIPost with constraint-based validation
- Add table-driven tests covering all validation paths
- Remove redundant isValidImageType checks from providers

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
